# /controllers — Request handlers (thin layer between routes and services)
# Controllers parse incoming requests, call the appropriate service, and send
# the HTTP response. They should contain NO business logic.
# Examples:
#   authController.js      → register, login, logout, refreshToken handlers
#   userController.js      → getProfile, updateProfile, deleteAccount
#   emissionController.js  → CRUD for carbon emission entries
#   reportController.js    → generateReport, getReportById, listReports
